article.headline: Austin Peay 57, E. Illinois 54
article.story: CLARKSVILLE, Tenn. -- Kyle Duncan scored 16 points and Drake Reed had 15 as Austin Peay rallied from a 10-point deficit to beat Eastern Illinois 57-54 Tuesday night in the first round of the Ohio Valley Conference Tournament. The Governors (18-12), the No. 2 seed, trailed the No. 7 seeded Panthers 42-32 with 16:47 left. Austin Peay finally pulled ahead 53-52 on a Marcel Williams jumper with 2:26 to play. The Panthers (12-18) regained the lead on two Romain Martin foul shots with 1:50 left. Reed tied the game at 54 with a free throw at 1:26, then Duncan made two free throws with 13 seconds remaining. A 3-point attempt by Billy Parrish bounced off the rim, Austin Peay rebounded, and Wes Channels made a free throw with 3 seconds left. Martin led Eastern Illinois with 20 points. Austin Peay will play No. 3 seed Murray State on Friday in Nashville.
